    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i just finished swapping the brake pads on my 2018 camry but every time i take it out for a quick test drive i hear this really high pitched squealing sound coming from the front left side. i didnt hear it before the swap. could it be a worn sensor or is the caliper stuck or something?",
