    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If it sounds like metal scraping, that's a more concerning sound than just a squeak, suggesting more than just a bedding-in issue. To check if the caliper is stuck, you can try manually rocking the caliper assembly while the car is safely jacked up, ensuring the pads have a little play. If the movement feels stiff or uneven, the caliper might be binding, which could be due to a seized slide pin or caliper guide. If the caliper moves freely, the issue is more likely related to pad material or rotor surface condition.",
