      "content": "Intermittent screeching that comes and goes without a clear trigger can be frustrating, and you're right to consider electrical or internal issues. While less common, a faulty ABS sensor or a wiring issue near the brake components could sometimes manifest as strange noises, though usually, those are more electronic alerts. Before diving into complex electrical diagnostics, try cleaning the rotor and pad surfaces thoroughly with a dedicated brake cleaner, as microscopic debris can cause intermittent noise. If cleaning doesn't help, the pads themselves might be incompatible with your rotors, or there could be a minor warping issue that only appears under certain loads.",
